{{notability|Academics|date=September 2015}} '''Frédéric Neyrat''' (born 1968) is Associate Professor in [https://clfs.wisc.edu/people/faculty/frederic-neyrat Comparative Literature at University of Wisconsin-Madison]. He is a French philosopher with an expertise in environmental humanities and contemporary theory. He was Program Director at the [[Collège international de philosophie]] in [[Paris]] and was also a fellow at Cornell's Society for the Humanities. He is a member of the editorial board of the review [[Multitudes]] and [https://www.editions-lignes.com/ Lignes]. Website: https://atoposophie.wordpress.com/
