{{about|the philosophical society|the mental health charity|Mind (charity)}}<!-- their charity commission listing emphasises that "we have no connection with ..." so there is evidently scope for confusion --> 

The '''Mind Association''' is a [[philosophy|philosophical]] [[learned society|society]] whose purpose is to promote the study of [[philosophy]]. The association publishes the journal ''[[Mind (journal)|Mind]]'' quarterly.

It was established in 1900 on the death of [[Henry Sidgwick]], who had supported ''Mind'' financially since 1891 and had suggested that after his death the society should be formed to oversee the journal.<ref name="continuum">{{cite encyclopedia|last=Preston|first=Aaron|editors=[[A.C. Grayling]], Naomi Goulder, [[Andrew Pyle (philosopher)|Andrew Pyle]]|encyclopedia=The Continuum Encyclopedia of British Philosophy|isbn=9780199754694|url=http://www.oxfordreference.com/view/10.1093/acref/9780199754694.001.0001/acref-9780199754694-e-1451|accessdate=17 January 2013}}</ref>

