{{Infobox philosopher |region = [[Western philosophy]] |era = [[Contemporary philosophy|21st century Philosophy]] |color = |image = |name = '''Stewart Duncan''' |birth_date = |birth_place = |death_date = |death_place = |school_tradition = [[Early modern philosophy]] | institutions = [[University of Florida]] |main_interests = Philosophy of [[Thomas Hobbes]] | thesis_title = | thesis_url = | thesis_year = | doctoral_advisor = | doctoral_students = |notable_ideas = | spouse = | education = | alma_mater = [[Rutgers University]] (Ph.D.), [[University of St Andrews]] (M.A.) |influences = |influenced = |awards = Humanities Scholarship Enhancement Fund Grant |website = http://users.clas.ufl.edu/sdrd/ }}
'''Stewart Duncan''' is an American philosopher and associate professor of philosophy at [[University of Florida]]. He is known for his expertise on [[early modern philosophy]] especially the materialist philosophy of [[Thomas Hobbes]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Sympathy and the Likeness Principle (with a nod to the Bentley-Newton correspondence) - New APPS: Art, Politics, Philosophy, Science|url=http://www.newappsblog.com/2013/07/sympathy-and-the-likeness-principle-with-a-nod-to-the-bentley-newton-correspondence.html|website=[[New APPS]]|accessdate=31 March 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|last1=Duncan|first1=Stewart|title=Review of Hobbes and the Law of Nature|journal=Notre Dame Philosophical Reviews|date=21 May 2010|url=https://ndpr.nd.edu/news/hobbes-and-the-law-of-nature/|accessdate=31 March 2018|issn=1538-1617}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|last1=Duncan|first1=Stewart|title=Review of Lessons from a Materialist Thinker: Hobbesian Reflections on Ethics and Politics|journal=Notre Dame Philosophical Reviews|date=5 August 2008|url=https://ndpr.nd.edu/news/lessons-from-a-materialist-thinker-hobbesian-reflections-on-ethics-and-politics/|accessdate=31 March 2018|issn=1538-1617}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|last1=Adams|first1=Marcus P.|title=Review of The Oxford Handbook of Hobbes|journal=Notre Dame Philosophical Reviews|date=22 November 2016|url=https://ndpr.nd.edu/news/the-oxford-handbook-of-hobbes/|accessdate=31 March 2018|issn=1538-1617}}</ref>
==Books== * ''Debates in Modern Philosophy: Essential Readings and Contemporary Responses'' (Routledge, 2013), edited with [[Antonia LoLordo]], {{ISBN|9780415887984}}
